HEADWORD: Bugleweed
<hw>Bu"gle*weed`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A plant of the Mint family and genus <gen>Lycopus</gen>; esp.
<spn>Lycopus Virginicus</spn>, which has mild narcotic and astringent
properties, and is sometimes used as a remedy for hemorrhage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bugloss</ent>⟦br⟧
